- Levenshtein implementation notes:
  - For short strings use full-matrix DP; for large strings consider banded or threshold-limited algorithms.
  - To compute edit operations or alignments, store back-pointers; otherwise use two-row optimization for scalar distance.
  - For transpositions use Damerau–Levenshtein variants.


